# Documentation Standards

All markdown files under `docs/` must follow these conventions.

## Frontmatter

Every document must include YAML frontmatter with:

```yaml
---
title: Human-readable document title
author-agent: role-name (e.g. product-owner, design-lead)
date: YYYY-MM-DD
status: draft | in-review | approved
---
```

- `title`: Short, clear title
- `author-agent`: Which agent role produced or last updated this doc
- `date`: Date of creation or last substantive update
- `status`: `draft` (work in progress), `in-review` (awaiting feedback), `approved` (accepted)

## Markdown Conventions

- Use ATX-style headers (`#`, `##`, `###`)
- Use relative links for cross-references within `docs/`: `[PRD](../product/prds/feature-x.md)`
- Use bullet lists for options or criteria; numbered lists for sequences
- Keep line length under 120 characters where practical for readability in diffs

## Version Tracking

- Do not maintain separate version numbers in filenames; use `date` in frontmatter and git history for versioning
- When making a breaking change to a doc that other agents depend on, update the `date` and set `status: draft` until dependent agents have been notified or have updated their work
